flow.descriptionCdata:
5c0d0ebb-f2bd-4025-ad0c-71c1ac20f839.64affa18-942b-422d-89b2-01062d56510d.description=
Exports a Virtual Machine as an Open Virtualization Format (OVF) package in a folder of files format to the local filesystem of the RAS.
The exported package consists of a .ovf descriptor file, .vmdk files for each vm disk and a .mf file that lists the SHA1 hashes for the .ovf and each .vmdk file.
If the Virtual Machine is in 'poweredOn' state, it will be shut down before the export.
Inputs\:
    host - VMware vCenter, ESX or ESXi host hostname or IP.
    user - VMware username.
    password - VMware user's password.
    port - Port to connect on.
Examples\: 443, 80
    protocol - Connection protocol.
Valid values\: "https", "http"
    virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. Inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/Folder/MyVM), Name of VM, IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123).
    path - Local directory path on the RAS to write the ovf template files.  The directory must already exists.
Examples\: "C\:\ovf_templates\exported_vm", "/ovf_templates/exported_vm"

Responses\:
    success - The flow completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The flow completed unsuccessfully.

Returns\:
    returnResult - Operation result or reason for failure.
    ovfPath - The path to the .ovf file that was generated on the local filesystem of the RAS.

Notes\:
Inventory Path Formatting\: If host is an ESX server inventory path will be\: ha-datacenter/vm/ .  If host is a vCenter the inventory path will be\: /vm// . The / part of the path is based on the "Virtual Machines & Templates" view in the vCenter client. The inventory path is case sensitive.
5c0d0ebb-f2bd-4025-ad0c-71c1ac20f839.6b19138d-444c-430d-8039-ca823f37f8d8.description=
Runs the ec2-import-instance command  from the EC2 API Tools. This command  creates a new import instance task  using metadata from the specified disk image, and imports the image to Amazon EC2.  

Inputs\:
    host - Hostname or ip address of the machine where you have installed the EC2 API Tools.
    port - Port number for connecting to the host.
    username - Username to connect as.
    password - Password of the user. If using a private key file this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
    protocol - The protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, REXEC, local, WMI, NASConnectTelnet, or HPOM).
    timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete; increase its value if you are getting incomplete output results or timeout.
    command - The command to execute.
    environment - Specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running command.
    startDir - The path to the starting directory.
    characterSet - The characterSet name for stream encoding and decoding between the RAS and target machine. For example, SJIS,EUC-JP, UTF-8.  By default it is UTF-8 (used by ssh, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, REXEC).
    instanceType - The type of instance to be launched.
Valid Values\: m1.small | m1.large | m1.xlarge | c1.medium | c1.xlarge | m2.xlarge | m2.2xlarge | m2.4xlarge
Default\: m1.small
    diskImageFilepath - The path to the disk image file.
Example\:  C\:\MyFiles\ImportVM\Exports\\w2k3r2-disk1.vmdk
    fileFormat - The file format of the disk image.
Valid Values\: VMDK | RAW | VHD
    architecture - The architecture of the image.
Valid Values\: i386 | x86_64
    s3BucketName - The Amazon S3 destination bucket for the manifest.
    accessKeyId - Access key ID of the bucket owner.
    accessKey - The secret access key of the bucket owner.
    otherArguments - Use this input if you want to add other non required options to the command.
Valid values\:  Visit http\://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/latest/CommandLineReference/ApiReference-cmd-ImportInstance.html for more info.

Responses\:
success - The command was executed successfully.
failure - The command could not be executed.

Notes\:
1. In order to use this operation you need to download & install the Amazon EC2 API Tools. You can find them at\: http\://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/SettingUp_CommandLine.html
The result of this operation is a conversion task. Use Describe Conversion Tasks operation to monitor it's status. Note that it might take several hours for the task to complete.
5c0d0ebb-f2bd-4025-ad0c-71c1ac20f839.7a4e4026-8b3e-4f2e-bcf9-4fd21a470b8b.prompt=Access Key\: 5c0d0ebb-f2bd-4025-ad0c-71c1ac20f839.9d1f6558-fa93-403d-b7ca-17587c0f289d.description=
Checks the status of a conversion task and if the task is completed it cleans the files used to perform the Import operation.

Inputs\:
    taskId - The conversion task id to be checked.
Example\: import-i-fhao5g5p
    accessKeyId - Access key ID of the bucket owner.
    accessKey - The secret access key of the bucket owner.
    proxyHost - The proxy server used to connect to Amazon.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port. You must either specify values for both  and  inputs or leave them both empty.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    serviceEndpoint - The endpoint to which requests are sent. 
    securityToken - The security token that you must pass to use the temporary credentials. You can generate this by using operations from the Security Token Service folder. You can only use the token together with the temporary credentials generated by the same operations.    
    deleteCreatedFiles - Specifies whether to delete the files generated by the OVF Export operation.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    thisFlowPath - The path to the flow that checks the status of the Import conversion task and cleans the results.
Default value\:  Library/Integrations/Amazon/EC2/VM Import/VMWare Windows Server 2008 Vm Import/Check Import Status
    centralHost - Hostname or IP address of the machine where the Export VM operation copied the OVF and VMDK files. This is the OO 10.x server where the Get Schedule Flow steps will run against.
    centralUsername - The username used to connect to the Central host.
    centralPassword - The password corresponding to the centralUsername user.
    centralPort - The port used to connect to the Central host.
    centralProtocol - The port used to connect to the Central host.
   
Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
5c0d0ebb-f2bd-4025-ad0c-71c1ac20f839.c35a7966-bea5-44aa-b397-2bfa3de507ef.description=
Gets a list of files and folders that reside in a directory.

Inputs\:
source - The directory to get the children of.
delimiter - A delimiter to put in between each child of this directory.

Returns\:
The list of paths to each child of this directory.

Extra Results\:
count - The total number of children of this directory.

Responses\:
success - children retrieved.
failure - operation failed.
5c0d0ebb-f2bd-4025-ad0c-71c1ac20f839.d8ed1480-9e5e-4a8e-9f75-074ebf11ccba.prompt=Access Key Id\: 5c0d0ebb-f2bd-4025-ad0c-71c1ac20f839.description=
Imports a Windows 2008 R2 virtual machine from VmWare 4.1.0 to the given Amazon account. This flow checks if all preconditions are met and if not it automatically sets the desired state on the target machine. In case you want to return to your initial settings it is recommended that you previously create a snapshot of the machine before running this operation. 

Inputs\:
    path - The path to the location where to export the VMDK file of the target machine. 
    username - The username for the imported virtual machine.
    password - The password for the imported virtual machine.
    vmHost -  VMware vCenter, ESX or ESXi host hostname or IP.
    vmUser - VMware username.
    vmPassword - VMware user's password.
    vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type.  
Valid values\: "inventorypath", "name", "ip", "hostname", "uuid", "vmid"
    virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. Inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/Folder/MyVM), Name of VM, IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123).
    rasHost - Hostname or ip address of the machine where you have installed the EC2 API Tools. It is recommended to use localhost.
    rasPort - Port number for connecting to the rasHost.
    rasUsername - Username for connecting to the rasHost.
    rasPassword - Password for connecting to the rasHost.
    protocol -  The protocol used to run the Amazon Import Instance command.
Valid values\: ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, REXEC, local, WMI, NASConnectTelnet, or HPOM
    instanceType - The type of instance to be launched.
Valid Values\: m1.small | m1.large | m1.xlarge | c1.medium | c1.xlarge | m2.xlarge | m2.2xlarge | m2.4xlarge
Default\: m1.medium
    architecture - The architecture of the image.
Valid values\: i386 | x86_64
    s3BucketName - The Amazon S3 destination bucket for the manifest.
    accessKeyId - Access key ID of the bucket owner.
    accessKey - The secret access key of the bucket owner.
    proxyHost - The proxy server used to connect to Amazon.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port. You must either specify values for both  and  inputs or leave them both empty.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    serviceEndpoint - The endpoint to which requests are sent. 
    securityToken - The security token that you must pass to use the temporary credentials. You can generate this by using operations from the Security Token Service folder. You can only use the token together with the temporary credentials generated by the same operations.
    deleteCreatedFiles - Specifies whether to delete the files generated by the OVF Export operation.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    statusFlowPath - The path to the flow that checks the status of the Import conversion task and cleans the results.
Default value\:  Library/Integrations/Amazon/EC2/VM Import/VMWare Windows Server 2008 Vm Import/Check Import Status

Results\:
    taskId- The Conversion Task Id created when importing the virtual machine into Amazon.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully. 
Notes\:
1. In order to use this operation you need to download & install the Amazon EC2 API Tools. You can find them at\: http\://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/SettingUp_CommandLine.html 
2. Please note that this operation includes also a schedule for the Check Import Status flow. Adapt the inputs of the scheduler to fit your own settings.
flow.name: Import Virtual Machine
